        },
        "subject": "LU-18687 build: refactor the top-level Makefile",
        "message": "LU-18687 build: refactor the top-level Makefile\n\nLustre uses automake far more than is strictly needed.\nLimit the top-level autoMakefile to only creating dist\ntarballs and handling install/deinstall. The remaining\nof make targets are transfered to a series of plain\nMakefiles. This completes our goal of building the\nLustre kernel modules without using automake.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: Icf32edb539443cd4d629d84f697e2a14767c316b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
